{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DdwYCM2f7AtUZWQjE4qXtw","type":"tool_result","content":"6eaa3f4 fix(web): align createApolloClient test with SYN-178 error masking\n---\n  fix/syn-205-emailupdate\n---\ncommit 206de3a74945f2160750421fc1193230e5d7b1c2\nAuthor: Smith the Agent <team+smith@thecodefoundry.dev>\nDate:   Tue Jul 14 22:39:34 2026 +0000\n\n    fix(web): surface email/whatsapp collision errors on member update (SYN-205)\n    \n    Apollo Client is configured with errorPolicy: 'all' (SYN-178), so\n    GraphQL errors from UpdateMemberDetails land in result.errors instead\n    of rejecting the mutation promise. UpdateMember.tsx's onSubmit relied\n    solely on a try/catch to detect the friendly email/whatsapp collision\n    check, which never fired under that error policy - so a rejected\n    write (duplicate email/whatsapp) was silently treated as a success:\n    the form ran its follow-up bacenta/basonta mutations, reset, and\n    navigated away with nothing actually saved. Meanwhile the app's\n    global errorLink independently surfaced a generic 'Something went\n    wrong' toast, matching the reported symptom exactly.\n    \n    Fix: onSubmit now inspects updateResult.errors explicitly. A\n    collision routes to the existing MemberCollisionDialog just like the\n    try/catch previously intended; any other GraphQL error surfaces a\n    toast via displayError and stops before the follow-up\n    mutations/navigation run. The original catch block stays in place as\n    a fallback for genuine thrown/network errors.\n    \n    Adds a focused regression test (UpdateMember.test.tsx) covering both\n    the collision path (dialog opens, no navigation) and the normal\n    success path (navigates away), rendering the real component against\n    a MockedProvider configured with errorPolicy: 'all' to match prod.\n    \n    Scope note: CreateMember.tsx and EditPage.tsx (self-profile edit)\n    share the same underlying pattern but are out of scope for this\n    ticket, which is specifically about the member-update flow.\n\n .../pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx   | 359 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .../src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.tsx    |  31 +-\n 2 files changed, 389 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019VwmAe8cPjMy8hT6rWpJsH","session_id":"1f8dd599-a4b3-4691-9eeb-51a7fceb4862","uuid":"0337b273-9f49-4feb-98d7-f68baa04b34f","timestamp":"2026-07-15T02:07:46.191Z","subagent_type":"code-reviewer","task_description":"Code review of SYN-205 email update fix"}
