{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017HQ7kWju9JFwsSeQbFn8B5","type":"tool_result","content":"ubuntu    324504  4.5  7.7 75167576 302448 pts/0 Sl+  02:01   0:24 claude -p You are Smith working ticket SYN-205 on fl-admin-portal (branch fix/syn-205-0909, base dev).  SCOPE — your ONLY job is to change code in THIS repo and write evidence. You do NOT manage the ticket's lifecycle: you have NO Atlassian/Jira MCP and you need none — do not search for one, do not try to move the ticket, do not report a 'transition failed'. The harness ALREADY moved this ticket to In Progress and will move it to Review, open the PR, and post to Slack after you finish. Ignore the ticket's Status field entirely.  TICKET: Key:       SYN-205 Type:      Bug Status:    Review Assignee:  Smith the Agent Labels:    client-reported,email,form-submission,member-profile Summary:   I get an error when I update a member’s profile that is the email --- BUG DESCRIPTIONWhen editing a member's profile and updating the email field, submitting the form results in an error message and the profile is not saved. The update fails instead of completing successfully.STEPS TO REPRODUCE1. Search for a member in the members list.2. Click the edit button on the member's profile.3. Paste a new value into the email field.4. Scroll down and click the submit button.EXPECTED BEHAVIOURThe profile is saved successfully with the updated email address and a success confirmation is shown.ACTUAL BEHAVIOURAn error message is displayed and the member's profile is not updated.ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA1. Submitting a valid updated email address on a member's profile saves the change successfully.2. A success message or confirmation is shown after a successful profile update.3. No error message appears when a valid email address is entered and submitted.4. The updated email address is reflected on the member's profile after saving.ENVIRONMENTNot specifiedPRIORITYHigh  COMMENTS (clarifications, decisions, decline feedback — obey the latest): [Smith the Agent] 🔨 Smith triaged SYN-205 as human-owned (Member profile updates likely involve auth flows and cross-tenant scope validation; root cause of email update failure is undiagnosed and ticket lacks specificity on which files/components to modify.) and is routing it to JD. A human (JD/Jesse/ddag) can hand it to Smith with an explicit override. [Smith the Agent] Root cause found and fixed.Apollo Client is configured with errorPolicy: 'all' (from SYN-178), so GraphQL errors from UpdateMemberDetails land in result.errors instead of rejecting the mutation promise. UpdateMember.tsx's onSubmit relied only on a try/catch to detect the backend's email/whatsapp collision check, which never fires under that policy. So when a member's new email collides with another member's, the write is correctly rejected server-side, but the client silently treated it as a success -- ran follow-up mutations, reset the form, and navigated away, while nothing was saved. A separate global error handler independently fired a generic \"Something went wrong\" toast, matching the reported symptom exactly.Fix: onSubmit now checks updateResult.errors explicitly and routes a real collision to the existing MemberCollisionDialog (same UX as it should have had before); any other GraphQL error surfaces a proper message and stops before follow-up mutations/navigation.Verified: tsc clean, full suite green (301/301, 19 files -- 299 pre-existing + 2 new regression tests covering both the collision and success paths).PR: https://github.com/firstlovecenter/fl-admin-portal/pull/555 (branch fix/syn-205-emailupdate -> dev)Scoped to the update flow only, per the ticket. CreateMember.tsx and the self-profile EditPage.tsx share the same underlying pattern -- flagging as a possible follow-up, not fixed here.Moving to Review for a human to check evidence and merge. [Smith the Agent] 🔨 A human directed Smith to work SYN-205 under an explicit override, despite triage flagging it human-owned (Ticket is underspecified—no error message details, no indication of which files to modify, root cause unknown, and email updates may involve auth/validation flows requiring human investigation.).  ATTACHMENTS: any files in .agent/attachments/ — READ them (the Read tool works on images and PDFs). A bug screenshot or mockup there is often the REAL spec; never work from the text alone if attachments exist. Video attachments are sampled into a <name>-frames/ subdir (one PNG per second, capped) — READ those frames to see what a screen-recording shows; the .mp4/.mov itself is not directly readable.  Read this repo's CLAUDE.md + kb/ first. Keep these gates green: - fl-cypher/no-interpolated-cypher. QUIRKS — obey them: - \"API is AWS Lambda (serverless) \\u2014 COLD STARTS are normal. Warm the GraphQL\\   \\ endpoint first and allow 60\\u2013120s for the initial 'Retrieving your church\\   \\ information' load before giving up.\" - \"Local browser testing needs the app's origin in the dev API CORS allowlist (127.0.0.1:5173,\\   \\ localhost:5173, localhost:3000 are allowlisted). Other origins: login works but\\   \\ every GraphQL call is CORS-blocked, so the dashboard never renders \\u2014 looks\\   \\ like a login loop but isn't.\" - \"Charts (ChurchGraph, TrendSpark) have NO test coverage \\u2014 visual QA of the\\   \\ drill-down is the REQUIRED gate; tsc + vite build passing is not sufficient.\" - \"PWA with a service worker \\u2014 use a fresh browser context / hard reload between\\   \\ runs to avoid stale cached assets or a cached old config.\"  LOCAL RUN + GATES (from the project config — use THESE commands, in the workdir given, to run and verify; dev endpoints + test account included): frontend:   build: npm run build   dev_auth: https://dev-auth.firstlovecenter.com   dev_graphql: https://dev-api-synago.firstlovecenter.com/graphql   run: npm start   test: npm run test:run   test_account: bacentaleader@test.com / password   workdir: web-react-ts