rs these per viewport), alt}.    PARITY IS REQUIRED: capture EVERY testing step at EVERY viewport in the project's evidence.viewports —    the shot count MUST match across Desktop/Tablet/Mobile (if a step, e.g. a drill-down result, has a    desktop shot it needs a tablet AND a mobile shot too, same caption). The app shows the viewports as    tabs, so a viewport missing a step reads as a gap. Same ordered steps, one shot per viewport per step.    followUps[] (OPTIONAL, 0-5 short strings): concrete follow-ups you DISCOVERED while fixing this but    did NOT do in this pass — e.g. \"`CustomLabel.tsx` is dead code, delete in a cleanup ticket\" or    \"the drill-down logic is duplicated across both charts, extract a shared hook\". A human turns these    into new tickets or dismisses them from the console, so only REAL, actionable findings; omit if none.    Do NOT set branch/commit/prUrl/jiraUrl/phase — the harness fills those. 4. Do NOT commit, push, open PRs, move the Jira ticket, or message Slack — and do NOT try to use any    Atlassian/Jira MCP (there isn't one on purpose; its absence is expected, not an error). The harness    owns ALL of that. End by summarising the change, the checks, and screenshots saved. --model claude-sonnet-5 --permission-mode bypassPermissions --mcp-config /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/.agent/mcp.json --output-format stream-json --verbose\nubuntu    324518  0.2  1.0 1068372 42452 pts/0   Sl+  02:02   0:01 npm exec @playwright/mcp@latest --headless --isolated --config /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/.agent/pw-config.json\nubuntu    324527  0.0  0.0 1252568 1940 pts/0    Sl+  02:02   0:00 /home/ubuntu/.local/bin/uv tool uvx mcp-neo4j-cypher@latest\nubuntu    324528  0.0  0.0 1260760 1940 pts/0    Sl+  02:02   0:00 /home/ubuntu/.local/bin/uv tool uvx mcp-neo4j-cypher@latest\nubuntu    324618  0.3  0.2 350528 10312 pts/0    Sl+  02:02   0:01 /home/ubuntu/.cache/uv/archive-v0/abpBRNvVORH52VKy/bin/pytho