{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Cd32re2PKMrtBkDtqZnwc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Review: `web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.tsx` + `UpdateMember.test.tsx` (SYN-205)\n\nI read both files end-to-end, the mutation SDL (`UpdateMutations.ts`), `MemberCollisionDialog.tsx`, `errorHandler.ts`, `createApolloClient.tsx`, and the backend collision error shape (`api/src/resolvers/utils/utils.ts`, `directory-resolvers.ts`) to confirm the fix's assumptions, then ran `tsc --noEmit`, `eslint`, and the new Vitest file.\n\n## Must Fix\n\n- `web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx` — **the added regression test suite does not pass.** Running it reproduces a failure on the exact test that is supposed to prove the fix:\n  ```\n  npx vitest run src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx\n  ...\n   ❯ src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx:321:38\n  Test Files  1 failed (1)\n       Tests  1 failed | 1 passed (2)\n  ```\n  `shows the collision dialog...` times out waiting for the dialog description; stderr shows `No more mocked responses for the query: memberBacentaSearch...` and `displayMemberBio...` — the `MEMBER_BACENTA_SEARCH` / `DISPLAY_MEMBER_BIO` / `DISPLAY_MEMBER_CHURCH` mocks are exhausted because the component fires those queries more times than mocks are supplied (re-running per submit-error branch fires more search/refetch calls than the success path does). Only `navigates away on a genuine successful update` passes in isolation.\n  Per CLAUDE.md, \"tests pass\" must be demonstrated by quoted runner output before landing — this suite currently fails and must not be presented as coverage for the fix. Fix: add extra `memberBacentaSearchMock`/`memberBioMock`/`memberChurchMock` instances (or a repeatable mock) sized to the actual number of calls the collision path triggers, and re-run to green.\n\n- `UpdateMember.tsx:149-152` — `displayError('There was an error updating the member profile', updateResult.errors[0])` passes a plain `GraphQLFormattedError` (per `@apollo/client`'s `FetchResult.errors?: ReadonlyArray<GraphQLFormattedError>`), not an `Error`/`ApolloError` instance. `getGraphQLErrorMessage` (`web-react-ts/src/utils/errorHandler.ts:8-37`) only special-cases those two types and otherwise falls back to `String(error)`. Verified: `String({ message: '...', extensions: {...} })` → `\"[object Object]\"`. So the toast shown to the user on any non-collision GraphQL error will read `\"[object Object]\"` instead of the real server message — a new, silent bug introduced by this exact fix, and it's untested (see next finding).\n  Fix: `displayError('...', new Error(updateResult.errors[0].message))`, or extend `getGraphQLErrorMessage` to also read `.message` off a plain `GraphQLFormattedError`.\n\n- `UpdateMember.tsx:156-174` — the fix only guards the primary `UpdateMember` mutation. `UpdateMemberBacenta` and `UpdateMemberBasonta` are called with the same `errorPolicy: 'all'` client and are **not** checked for `.errors`. If either returns a GraphQL error (e.g. a bacenta-transfer collision/validation failure), the promise still resolves normally, execution falls through to `onSubmitProps.resetForm(); navigate('/member/displaydetails')`, and the user sees exactly the SYN-205 symptom this ticket fixes — just for the bacenta/basonta reassignment instead of the email field. This is inside the same function this PR is patching (not the explicitly out-of-scope `CreateMember.tsx`/`EditPage.tsx`), so it should be closed in this PR: check `.errors` on both results the same way, or bail out with `displayError` before continuing.\n\n- `UpdateMember.tsx:136` — `updateResult.errors.find((err: any) => err?.extensions?.collision)` introduces a new `any` in modified code, which CLAUDE.md's TypeScript section forbids unconditionally (\"No `any` in new or modified code\"). `GraphQLFormattedError.extensions` is typed `Record<string, unknown> | undefined`, so this can be typed without `any`, e.g.:\n  ```ts\n  const collisionInfo = updateResult.errors.find(\n    (err): err is typeof err & { extensions: { collision: MemberCollision } } =>\n      Boolean((err.extensions as { collision?: unknown } | undefined)?.collision)\n  )?.extensions.collision as MemberCollision | undefined\n  ```\n  or a small typed helper — not a bare `any` parameter.\n\n## Should Fix\n\n- `UpdateMember.test.tsx` — no test exercises the third branch added by this diff: a non-collision GraphQL error (`updateResult.errors[0]` with no `extensions.collision`) that should hit `displayError` and stop before the follow-up mutations. This is precisely the branch that contains the `[object Object]` bug above — a test here would have caught it. Add a mock that returns a plain `errors: [{ message: '...' }]` (no `collision` extension) and assert `displayError`/toast content and `mockNavigate` not called.\n- `UpdateMember.tsx:127-133` — 7-line comment block explaining the `errorPolicy: 'all'` rationale. CLAUDE.md's comment-hygiene rule flags multi-line comment blocks as a smell to be moved into a kb/ADR note rather than inline. Trim to a one-line pointer (e.g. `// errorPolicy: 'all' (SYN-178) — GraphQL errors land in .errors, not a rejection. See kb/... or SYN-205.`) and let the ticket/PR description carry the narrative.\n- `UpdateMember.tsx:179-192` — the pre-existing `catch` block's `error?.graphQLErrors?.find(...)` duplicates the new collision-extraction logic against a different error shape. Given `errorPolicy: 'all'`, this branch is now effectively dead for GraphQL errors from `UpdateMember` (only reachable for a genuine network/thrown error, which won't carry `graphQLErrors`). Either remove the now-redundant collision check here (keep just the generic `throwToSentry`), or add a one-line comment stating explicitly it's intentional defense-in-depth so a future reader doesn't assume it's still live for the GraphQL case.\n- Interaction with `web-react-ts/src/lib/createApolloClient.tsx:122-145` (not touched by this diff, but directly governs the flow being fixed): the global `errorLink` toasts a generic `\"Something went wrong\"` for every GraphQL error whose message doesn't include `'Unauthenticated'` — including the collision error. So every collision now surfaces **both** the friendly `MemberCollisionDialog` **and** a generic \"Something went wrong\" toast simultaneously, which partially reproduces the confusing double-messaging called out in the ticket's own root-cause analysis. Worth a fast follow-up to have `errorLink` skip toasting for `extensions.code === 'BAD_USER_INPUT'` errors, since callers that explicitly handle those (like this one) already give the user better feedback.\n\n## Consider\n\n- `updateResult.errors` is a deprecated field on Apollo Client's `FetchResult` type in the installed version (3.14) — its own `.d.ts` states `\"errors will no longer be available on the result in Apollo Client 4.0 ... consolidated to the error property.\"` Not urgent, but worth a note for whoever eventually bumps Apollo Client major versions, since this code (and the pattern it's modeled on) will need to switch to reading `result.error`.\n\n## What I checked and found clean\n\n- `isAuth`/permission concerns: N/A — this is a pure frontend form-submission change, no resolver touched.\n- Church-context / ADR-007: no church IDs read from local state or URL params here.\n- Routing (ADR-004): no route changes.\n- Styling / Shadcn+Tailwind: no markup changed; `MemberCollisionDialog` (unchanged) already uses Shadcn primitives.\n- PWA/mobile: no new UI surface introduced by this diff.\n- `tsc --noEmit` and `eslint --max-warnings=0` both pass clean on the two files.\n- Backend collision payload shape (`api/src/resolvers/utils/utils.ts:21-52`) matches the `MemberCollision` type consumed here — no cross-package drift.\n- Scope note in the commit message (CreateMember.tsx / EditPage.tsx sharing the same errorPolicy issue but being out of scope) is accurate — I confirmed neither file currently has any collision-handling logic, so this PR isn't leaving a half-migrated pattern behind in those files.\n\nFiles reviewed: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.tsx`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/MemberCollisionDialog.tsx`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMutations.ts`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/utils/errorHandler.ts`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/web-react-ts/src/lib/createApolloClient.tsx`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/api/src/resolvers/utils/utils.ts`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3998,"cache_read_input_tokens":62675,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3998,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019VwmAe8cPjMy8hT6rWpJsH","session_id":"1f8dd599-a4b3-4691-9eeb-51a7fceb4862","uuid":"2ab87961-d74f-439c-a982-454bc2cf7f1a","request_id":"req_011Cd32rcwPsd4YBnRN3iK53","subagent_type":"code-reviewer","task_description":"Code review of SYN-205 email update fix"}
