{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Cd33fimwcX6XyagAFirEK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016w2vuiZ6kjzmTmP565ciYV","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Re-review SYN-205 fix after addressing findings","subagent_type":"code-reviewer","prompt":"You (or a peer instance) reviewed an earlier version of the working-tree diff on branch fix/syn-205-0909 in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal and found these issues, which have now been addressed:\n\n1. \"Must Fix\" — new regression test failed. (Root cause turned out to be a temporary git stash the author had applied during browser testing, unrelated to the code; the fix was in place all along. Re-verify tests pass now.)\n2. \"Must Fix\" — `displayError('...', updateResult.errors[0])` passed a plain GraphQLFormattedError (not an Error/ApolloError instance) into `getGraphQLErrorMessage`, which fell through to `String(error)` → \"[object Object]\" in the toast. Fix applied: `getGraphQLErrorMessage` in web-react-ts/src/utils/errorHandler.ts now also reads `.message` off any plain object with a string `message` property; call sites now wrap with `new Error(result.errors[0].message)`.\n3. \"Must Fix\" — `UpdateMemberBacenta`/`UpdateMemberBasonta` follow-up mutations (same function, same errorPolicy: 'all' client) were not checked for `.errors`, so a bacenta/basonta-transfer GraphQL error would silently \"succeed\" the same way the original bug did for email. Fix applied: both are now checked with `bacentaResult.errors?.length` / `basontaResult.errors?.length`, calling `displayError` and returning before the form resets/navigates.\n4. \"Must Fix\" — a bare `any` was used in `(err: any) => err?.extensions?.collision` in newly-added code. Fix applied: extracted a typed `extractCollision(errors: readonly { extensions?: unknown }[] | undefined): MemberCollision | undefined` helper (module-level, above the component) that both the new `updateResult.errors` path and the pre-existing `catch` block's `error?.graphQLErrors` path now share — no `any` in the new code, and the duplicate collision-extraction logic is deduplicated.\n5. \"Should Fix\" — no test covered the non-collision GraphQL error branch. Fix applied: added a third test in UpdateMember.test.tsx (`shows a real error toast (does not navigate away) for a non-collision GraphQL error`) that mocks `sonner`'s `toast` (matching the pattern in web-react-ts/src/lib/createApolloClient.test.tsx) and asserts `toast.error` receives the real message, not \"[object Object]\".\n6. \"Should Fix\" — trimmed the 7-line comment explaining errorPolicy: 'all' down to a 4-line one.\n\nNot addressed (left as-is, judged out of scope for this pass — confirm you agree or flag if you don't):\n- The pre-existing `catch` block's collision check is now effectively dead for GraphQL errors from the primary UpdateMember mutation (only reachable for genuine network/thrown errors) — left in place as defense-in-depth, not removed.\n- The global `errorLink` in createApolloClient.tsx double-toasting alongside the collision dialog — flagged as a follow-up, not fixed (touches shared error-handling behavior used app-wide, outside this ticket's scope).\n- A pre-existing IDOR gap in `UpdateMemberDetails` resolver (missing `assertScopeViaMember`, unrelated to this diff) — flagged as a follow-up for a separate ticket, not fixed here (backend, not part of SYN-205's email-update-flow scope).\n\nRun `git diff dev -- web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.tsx web-react-ts/src/pages/directory/update/UpdateMember.test.tsx web-react-ts/src/utils/errorHandler.ts` to see the current full diff, then re-run `npx tsc -p tsconfig.json --noEmit`, `npx eslint <the three files> --max-warnings=0`, and `npm run test:run -- UpdateMember` yourself to confirm green (do not trust my claim — verify). Confirm whether all four \"Must Fix\" items and the \"Should Fix\" test-coverage item are actually resolved, and give a final ship/no-ship verdict."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":422,"cache_read_input_tokens":152583,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":422},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f8dd599-a4b3-4691-9eeb-51a7fceb4862","uuid":"fd71dc25-e6e8-4244-bbff-698761f37d20","request_id":"req_011Cd33fXSokkypF2ERkjfxN"}
