{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JezYo2vvRLkMm4Xq4JVbgK","type":"tool_result","content":"ubuntu    324504  3.4  8.5 75200344 333216 pts/0 Sl+  02:01   1:15 claude -p You are Smith working ticket SYN-205 on fl-admin-portal (branch fix/syn-205-0909, base dev).  SCOPE — your ONLY job is to change code in THIS repo and write evidence. You do NOT manage the ticket's lifecycle: you have NO Atlassian/Jira MCP and you need none — do not search for one, do not try to move the ticket, do not report a 'transition failed'. The harness ALREADY moved this ticket to In Progress and will move it to Review, open the PR, and post to Slack after you finish. Ignore the ticket's Status field entirely.  TICKET: Key:       SYN-205 Type:      Bug Status:    Review Assignee:  Smith the Agent Labels:    client-reported,email,form-submission,member-profile Summary:   I get an error when I update a member’s profile that is the email --- BUG DESCRIPTIONWhen editing a member's profile and updating the email field, submitting the form results in an error message and the profile is not saved. The update fails instead of completing successfully.STEPS TO REPRODUCE1. Search for a member in the members list.2. Click the edit button on the member's profile.3. Paste a new value into the email field.4. Scroll down and click the submit button.EXPECTED BEHAVIOURThe profile is saved successfully with the updated email address and a success confirmation is shown.ACTUAL BEHAVIOURAn error message is displayed and the member's profile is not updated.ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA1. Submitting a valid updated email address on a member's profile saves the change successfully.2. A success message or confirmation is shown after a successful profile update.3. No error message appears when a valid email address is entered and submitted.4. The updated email address is reflected on the member's profile after saving.ENVIRONMENTNot specifiedPRIORITYHigh  COMMENTS (clarifications, decisions, decline feedback — obey the latest): [Smith the Agent] 🔨 Smith triaged SYN-205 as human-owned (Member profile updates likely involve auth flows and cross-tenant scope validation; root cause of email update failure is undiagnosed and ticket lacks specificity on which files/components to modify.) and is routing it to JD. A human (JD/Jesse/ddag) can hand it to Smith with an explicit override. [Smith the Agent] Root cause found and fixed.Apollo Client is configured with errorPolicy: 'all' (from SYN-178), so GraphQL errors from UpdateMemberDetails land in result.errors instead of rejecting the mutation promise. UpdateMember.tsx's onSubmit relied only on a try/catch to detect the backend's email/whatsapp collision check, which never fires under that policy. So when a member's new email collides with another member's, the write is correctly rejected server-side, but the client silently treated it as a success -- ran follow-up mutations, reset the form, and navigated away, while nothing was saved. A separate global error handler independently fired a generic \"Something went wrong\" toast, matching the reported symptom exactly.Fix: onSubmit now checks updateResult.errors explicitly and routes a real collision to the existing MemberCollisionDialog (same UX as it should have had before); any other GraphQL error surfaces a proper message and stops before follow-up mutations/navigation.Verified: tsc clean, full suite green (301/301, 19 files -- 299 pre-existing + 2 new regression tests covering both the collision and success paths).PR: https://github.com/firstlovecenter/fl-admin-portal/pull/555 (branch fix/syn-205-emailupdate -> dev)Scoped to the update flow only, per the ticket. CreateMember.tsx and the self-profile EditPage.tsx share the same underlying pattern -- flagging as a possible follow-up, not fixed here.Moving to Review for a human to check evidence and merge. [Smith the Agent] 🔨 A human directed Smith to work SYN-205 under an explicit override, despite triage flagging it human-owned (Ticket is underspecified—no error message details, no indication of which files to modify, root cause unknown, and email updates may involve auth/validation flows requiring human investigation.).  ATTACHMENTS: any files in .agent/attachments/ — READ them (the Read tool works on images and PDFs). A bug screenshot or mockup there is often the REAL spec; never work from the text alone if attachments exist. Video attachments are sampled into a <name>-frames/ subdir (one PNG per second, capped) — READ those frames to see what a screen-recording shows; the .mp4/.mov itself is not directly readable.  Read this repo's CLAUDE.md + kb/ first. Keep these gates green: - fl-cypher/no-interpolated-cypher. QUIRKS — obey them: - \"API is AWS Lambda (serverless) \\u2014 COLD STARTS are normal. Warm the GraphQL\\   \\ endpoint first and allow 60\\u2013120s for the initial 'Retrieving your church\\   \\ information' load before giving up.\" - \"Local browser testing needs the app's origin in the dev API CORS allowlist (127.0.0.1:5173,\\   \\ localhost:5173, localhost:3000 are allowlisted). Other origins: login works but\\   \\ every GraphQL call is CORS-blocked, so the dashboard never renders \\u2014 looks\\   \\ like a login loop but isn't.\" - \"Charts (ChurchGraph, TrendSpark) have NO test coverage \\u2014 visual QA of the\\   \\ drill-down is the REQUIRED gate; tsc + vite build passing is not sufficient.\" - \"PWA with a service worker \\u2014 use a fresh browser context / hard reload between\\   \\ runs to avoid stale cached assets or a cached old config.\"  LOCAL RUN + GATES (from the project config — use THESE commands, in the workdir given, to run and verify; dev endpoints + test account included): frontend:   build: npm run build   dev_auth: https://dev-auth.firstlovecenter.com   dev_graphql: https://dev-api-synago.firstlovecenter.com/graphql   run: npm start   test: npm run test:run   test_account: bacentaleader@test.com / password   workdir: web-react-ts  Do: 1. Make the smallest correct change; run the pinned build + test gates above (fallback if a project    pins none: tsc + build + tests). Compare tsc/test results to the base    branch so you distinguish NEW failures (yours to fix) from pre-existing ones (note, don't fix). 2. If the change has a VISIBLE surface, use the Playwright browser MCP (mcp__playwright) to capture    before/after screenshots into .agent/shots/ — one PNG per state PER VIEWPORT below, named    <state>-<viewport>.png. Obey the quirks (dev server, test account, cold-start waits, CORS origin    127.0.0.1:5173). If the change is not visual, skip screenshots.    Your whole browser session is being SCREEN-RECORDED automatically for the report — so drive the    fix's flow through the browser MCP, and when you are COMPLETELY finished with the browser call the    MCP's browser_close so the recording is saved. Do NOT set videos[] yourself; the harness attaches it.    Viewports for this project: - frame: desktop   height: 900   name: desktop   width: 1440 - frame: tablet   height: 1180   name: tablet   width: 820 - frame: mobile   height: 844   name: mobile   width: 390 3. Write .agent/report.json (the evidence manifest the smith-reports app renders). The report must    answer three questions in order — What was the bug? · What did you change? · What's the proof? — so:    type, labels[], title,    bug (1-3 sentences: what was BROKEN and its user-visible impact — the report's \"The bug\" section),    summary (what you CHANGED to fix it; `code` + **bold** allowed — the \"What changed\" section),    evidenceNote,    checks[] (REAL results, e.g. [{\"label\":\"tsc\",\"pass\":true},{\"label\":\"Build\",\"pass\":true},{\"label\":\"Tests\",\"pass\":true}]),    and shots[] — the PROOF. One per PNG: {file, frame:desktop|tablet|mobile, width, height,    tag:before|after|verify, label (short location tag, e.g. \"HOME DASHBOARD\"),    caption (the testing STEP this shot proves, as one full sentence — the app numbers these per viewport), alt}.    PARITY IS REQUIRED: capture EVERY testing step at EVERY viewport in the project's evidence.viewports —    the shot count MUST match across Desktop/Tablet/Mobile (if a step, e.g. a drill-down result, has a    desktop shot it needs a tablet AND a mobile shot too, same caption). The app shows the viewports as    tabs, so a viewport missing a step reads as a gap. Same ordered steps, one shot per viewport per step.    followUps[] (OPTIONAL, 0-5 short strings): concrete follow-ups you DISCOVERED while fixing this but    did NOT do in this pass — e.g. \"`CustomLabel.tsx` is dead code, delete in a cleanup ticket\" or    \"the drill-down logic is duplicated across both charts, extract a shared hook\". A human turns these    into new tickets or dismisses them from the console, so only REAL, actionable findings; omit if none.    Do NOT set branch/commit/prUrl/jiraUrl/phase — the harness fills those. 4. Do NOT commit, push, open PRs, move the Jira ticket, or message Slack — and do NOT try to use any    Atlassian/Jira MCP (there isn't one on purpose; its absence is expected, not an error). The harness    owns ALL of that. End by summarising the change, the checks, and screenshots saved. --model claude-sonnet-5 --permission-mode bypassPermissions --mcp-config /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/repos/fl-admin-portal/.agent/mcp.json --output-format stream-json --verbose","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f8dd599-a4b3-4691-9eeb-51a7fceb4862","uuid":"b89a621a-3dc7-4ae4-b995-020ebcf25af1","timestamp":"2026-07-15T02:38:26.283Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"ubuntu    324504  3.4  8.5 75200344 333216 pts/0 Sl+  02:01   1:15 claude -p You are Smith working ticket SYN-205 on fl-admin-portal (branch fix/syn-205-0909, base dev).  SCOPE — your ONLY job is to change code in THIS repo and write evidence. You do NOT manage the ticket's lifecycle: you have NO Atlassian/Jira MCP and you need none — do not search for one, do not try to move 