e.\",","+    \"api/src/resolvers/directory/directory-resolvers.ts's UpdateMemberDetails resolver is missing an assertScopeViaMember(context, args.id) check (unlike its siblings UpdateMemberBacenta/ReactivateMemberToBacenta in the same file) — a Bacenta-level leader/admin can currently edit any member's profile org-wide by ID. Pre-existing, unrelated to this fix, but a real IDOR worth its own ticket.\",","+    \"The global errorLink in lib/createApolloClient.tsx toasts a generic \\\"Something went wrong\\\" for every GraphQL error, including ones already given better UX by a caller (e.g. the collision dialog here) — so collisions now show both the friendly dialog and a redundant generic toast. Consider skipping the generic toast when extensions.collision (or a BAD_USER_INPUT-style code) is present.\"","   ]"," }"]}],"originalFile":"{\n  \"type\": \"Task\",\n  \"labels\": [\"smith-followup\"],\n  \"title\": \"Delete CustomLabel.tsx — confirmed dead code\",\n  \"bug\": \"`web-react-ts/src/components/pie-chart/CustomLabel.tsx` (a recharts pie-chart label component) had zero importers anywhere in the app. It was flagged as dead code while working SYN-201 but left untouched there; it has been sitting in the tree ever since with no code path reaching it, adding dead weight to the bundle for no user-facing benefit.\",\n  \"summary\": \"Deleted `web-react-ts/src/components/pie-chart/CustomLabel.tsx`. Before removing it, verified with repo-wide `grep` for both `CustomLabel` and `pie-chart` that nothing imports it — no relative import, no barrel re-export, no dynamic `import()`/`require()` string, and no test file references it. Confirmed again after deletion that the search returns zero hits.\",\n  \"evidenceNote\": \"This is a pure dead-code deletion with zero importers and no rendered UI surface, so no before/after screenshots apply. Proof is the verification gates below plus an independent `code-reviewer` pass that re-ran the same reference search and found no remaining callers.\",\n  \"checks\": [\n    { \"label\": \"tsc --noEmit\", \"pass\": true },\n    { \"label\": \"Build (vite)\", \"pass\": true },\n    { \"label\": \"Tests (288/289 passing; 1 pre-existing failure in createApolloClient.test.tsx confirmed present on base commit via git stash, unrelated to this change)\", \"pass\": true },\n    { \"label\": \"code-reviewer (no importers found, deletion confirmed safe)\", \"pass\": true }\n  ],\n  \"shots\": [],\n  \"followUps\": [\n    \"`CustomLegend.tsx` and `PieChart.css` in the same `pie-chart/` directory are now fully orphaned (zero remaining importers) — delete them together in a follow-up cleanup ticket.\",\n    \"`web-react-ts/kb/02-design-system.md:88` and `.claude/commands/new-component.md:41` still reference `components/pie-chart` as a chart component/example folder to keep — update those once the directory is fully removed.\"\n  ]\n}\n","userModified":false}}
