{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Cd34yPqXuyCfzpSGxQbNp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in order. Here's the summary:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Bug (SYN-205):** `UpdateMember.tsx` only detected mutation errors via a try/catch, but Apollo Client's `errorPolicy: 'all'` (from SYN-178) routes GraphQL errors into `result.errors` instead of rejecting the promise. A rejected write — most commonly an email/WhatsApp collision — was silently treated as success: the form ran follow-up mutations, reset, and navigated away with nothing actually saved, while an unrelated global handler fired a generic \"Something went wrong\" toast. Reproduced this exactly against the live dev database, matching the attached bug screenshot.\n\n**Fix:**\n- `onSubmit` now checks `updateResult.errors` explicitly, routing real collisions to the existing `MemberCollisionDialog` and any other error to `displayError`, returning before follow-up mutations/navigation.\n- Applied the same `.errors` guard to the `UpdateMemberBacenta`/`UpdateMemberBasonta` follow-up calls, which had the identical gap.\n- Extracted a typed `extractCollision()` helper (removes a stray `any`, dedupes logic).\n- Fixed `errorHandler.ts`'s `getGraphQLErrorMessage` to read `.message` off plain `GraphQLFormattedError` objects, closing a `\"[object Object]\"` toast bug found during review.\n\n**Checks:** tsc clean · eslint clean · build clean · **308/308 tests passing** (302 pre-existing + 6 new: 3 in `UpdateMember.test.tsx` covering collision/success/non-collision-error paths, 3 in new `errorHandler.test.ts`).\n\n**Review:** `code-reviewer` and `security-reviewer` both ran; all Must-Fix findings were addressed and verified in a follow-up review pass (verdict: **Ship**). Security review found no Critical/High issues in the diff itself, and flagged one pre-existing backend IDOR gap (unrelated, noted as a follow-up).\n\n**Evidence:** 9 screenshots in `.agent/shots/` (before/after/verify × desktop/tablet/mobile), captured by toggling the fix in the working tree against the real dev GraphQL API — confirming the bug reproduction, the collision dialog now firing correctly, and a genuine successful save with the updated email persisted.\n\n**Follow-ups noted** (not fixed here): `CreateMember.tsx`/`EditPage.tsx` share the same errorPolicy pattern; a pre-existing IDOR gap in the `UpdateMemberDetails` resolver; and the global error link double-toasting alongside the collision dialog."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":447,"cache_read_input_tokens":325036,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":447},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f8dd599-a4b3-4691-9eeb-51a7fceb4862","uuid":"bed03343-cbcf-4e99-8d9f-62ca9c165e32","request_id":"req_011Cd34yHGtgpJ9qYriLseu6"}
